issues.description: The problem statement text instructs students to add attributes named `inscribedStudents` and `guestStudents`, but the UML diagram (and the template/solution code) define these attributes as `numberOfInscribedStudents` and `numberOfGuestStudents`. This naming mismatch could confuse students when implementing getters/setters and matching tests.
issues.suggested_fix: Update the problem statement text to refer to the attributes as `numberOfInscribedStudents` and `numberOfGuestStudents` to match the UML diagram and provided code.
